#text=The glorious ocean turned to sight, The bluest devils then gave way Before the genial month of May -.

#text=Who calls it April, he is wrong, For May it is in northern tongue, The month of love, the month of song, The olive's everlasting leaf O'erhangs the green field fair and brief; Dashes along the sparkling rile, Greeting the valley from the hile; With joy and life each hamlet teems, A bridal-bed the country seems, Reminding of the Persians tale, How was courted the rose by the nightingale.
#text=But, dearest Brunn, what's that to You?
#text=You do not understand, t'is true* My boon companion though thou art, Whom I do love with all my heart, In every language, every clime, In honest prose and doggrel rhyme.
#text=Write english still, though you can't soell.
